31:55.340 --> 31:58.685
It's not enough.

31:58.740 --> 32:00.640
- Found it.

32:01.870 --> 32:05.306
- Yeah, I can feel an abnormal
nodule right here.

32:05.350 --> 32:07.818
I'm gonna cut it out,
send it to pathology.

32:08.830 --> 32:12.709
- Is it crazy I'm happy
Dr. Reynolds found a tumor

32:12.750 --> 32:13.830
in my mom's bowel?

32:13.880 --> 32:16.440
- No, you're not crazy.

32:16.490 --> 32:19.573
Come with me,
you gave me an idea.

32:25.980 --> 32:28.448
Thank you all for coming.
- He is canning us.

32:28.510 --> 32:29.932
-Hmm?

32:29.990 --> 32:31.503
- It's just like that scene
in "Goodfellas"

32:31.550 --> 32:32.812
when they tell Joe Pesci
he's gonna get made

32:32.860 --> 32:34.373
and he's all excited
and dressed up,

32:34.430 --> 32:35.727
and then he goes in the room,
and whack!

32:35.770 --> 32:37.943
They whack him.
- I am not whacking you.

32:37.990 --> 32:40.732
I'm hiring you, all of you.

32:40.780 --> 32:42.828
We're opening a new clinic
in Sheepshead Bay.

32:42.870 --> 32:44.997
And since you're all
on payroll already,

32:45.050 --> 32:47.689
this will actually be the first
profitable thing I've done.

32:47.740 --> 32:49.002
- Sheepshead Bay?

32:49.050 --> 32:50.745
- New Amsterdam runs
satellite clinics

32:50.790 --> 32:52.485
all over the city,
but we've neglected this part

32:52.530 --> 32:53.838
of Brooklyn and the people
who live there,

32:53.880 --> 32:56.667
and that ends today
with your help.

32:56.710 --> 32:58.871
- Sounds great,
but I'm kinda over

32:58.930 --> 33:01.012
the parking attendant thing.

33:01.060 --> 33:03.665
- Good, because you'll be
running our reception area.

33:03.720 --> 33:05.881
Greeting people,
making sure they feel at ease.

33:05.940 --> 33:07.669
- That I can do.

33:07.720 --> 33:10.416
- Anna, you'll be installing
our new computer systems.

33:10.460 --> 33:12.542
- Linux or DOS?
- No idea.

33:12.590 --> 33:15.024
And Jessica, you'll be
caring for the community

33:15.080 --> 33:17.025
who raised you
and who needs you now.

33:17.080 --> 33:19.378
- Thank you, Max.

33:19.430 --> 33:21.819
- Hello?
I hope I'm not too late.

33:21.860 --> 33:25.387
- Everyone, meet our new
radiology department.

33:41.140 --> 33:42.357
- You're gonna need
the suture kit.

33:42.410 --> 33:44.708
- Yeah.

34:41.990 --> 34:43.639
- Ask me again.

34:48.170 --> 34:50.866
- What are you running from?

35:03.230 --> 35:06.961
I told my mom that
I was going to NYU.

35:07.010 --> 35:10.013
That I'd be here in town,
close by.

35:12.240 --> 35:15.880
Dad had died the year before,
and things had gotten...

35:17.720 --> 35:20.234
I didn't even tell her that
I applied to Whitman.

35:22.030 --> 35:24.112
I didn't tell Vanessa,
my sister.

35:27.600 --> 35:30.945
And I knew...

35:30.990 --> 35:35.689
I knew that they wouldn't be
okay without me.

35:37.000 --> 35:40.174
I mean, I protected Vanessa.

35:40.220 --> 35:43.872
She thought I was a rock star.

35:43.920 --> 35:47.174
But she was 12...

35:47.230 --> 35:50.927
I mean, I couldn't--I couldn't
take her with me.

35:52.710 --> 35:55.178
I wanted to,

35:55.240 --> 35:57.231
but I knew ifI didn't go...

35:58.980 --> 36:00.880
Then I was never gonna get out.

36:06.250 --> 36:10.687
One night, I...
Itucked her up in bed...

36:14.820 --> 36:16.299
And I left.

36:16.340 --> 36:19.514
I, um...

36:19.560 --> 36:21.949
I left my little sister.

36:25.570 --> 36:29.529
She's in rehab now, again.

36:29.570 --> 36:30.787
Fourth time.

36:30.840 --> 36:32.705
- That is not on you.

36:34.270 --> 36:36.090
- I could have saved her,
you know?

36:36.150 --> 36:37.833
I mean, I could have saved
my mom.

36:37.890 --> 36:39.278
- You were a kid,
that is not your job.

36:39.320 --> 36:41.231
- Then whose was it?

36:41.280 --> 36:44.750
I mean, I was all they had,
and then I just--I just left.

36:46.110 --> 36:48.578
- Listen to me.

36:48.640 --> 36:50.722
There are people
all over the world

36:50.770 --> 36:52.897
with families just like yours.

36:52.940 --> 36:54.988
All over the world.

36:55.030 --> 36:58.682
And many of them,
most of them,

36:58.730 --> 37:00.595
they never get out.

37:03.130 --> 37:05.303
You saved the only person
that you could save.

37:05.350 --> 37:07.079
You did not fail.

37:07.130 --> 37:09.655
What you did was an act of
incredible strength.

37:13.400 --> 37:15.618
- I don't feel strong.

37:19.140 --> 37:21.927
- You only have to be strong
enough to do one more thing.

37:29.370 --> 37:32.066
I need help.

37:32.110 --> 37:33.987
- Okay.

37:35.770 --> 37:37.818
We can do that.

37:37.860 --> 37:39.293
Okay?

37:43.340 --> 37:44.989
- Were you, uh,

37:45.040 --> 37:47.167
were you really clearing me
to go back to work?

37:48.390 --> 37:50.858
- And let a drug addict loose
in the ED?

37:52.000 --> 37:53.262
God, no.

37:53.310 --> 37:56.302
- You kidding me?

37:59.010 --> 38:01.615
- Throw away your things

38:01.670 --> 38:05.788
When this is over

38:09.850 --> 38:12.978
Oh, when the ice

38:13.020 --> 38:15.159
Is melted away

38:17.380 --> 38:21.157
And the hunger returns

38:21.210 --> 38:23.986
I will be the same

38:24.040 --> 38:26.031
- Hey.

38:26.080 --> 38:28.207
- Hey.

38:29.740 --> 38:32.345
- I wasn't expecting
to see you.

38:32.390 --> 38:34.176
- Because I cut you off
at the knees?

38:34.220 --> 38:38.008
- I came on too strong.
It's a personality defect.

38:38.050 --> 38:41.042
- No, you didn't, and it's not.

38:41.100 --> 38:44.831
It was spontaneous and fun

38:44.880 --> 38:47.189
and completely lovely.

38:49.020 --> 38:52.888
And that's what made it
utterly terrifying for me.

38:57.810 --> 39:00.119
I haven't wanted to _take
a chance on something--

39:00.160 --> 39:04.073
um, on someone
in a really long time.

39:04.120 --> 39:07.772
I mean, I used to be
a person who took chances,

39:07.820 --> 39:09.299
and I really wanna be
that person again.

39:09.340 --> 39:10.864
- You don't have to explain.

39:10.910 --> 39:12.161
- No, I want to.

39:12.210 --> 39:14.212
You make me want to.

39:16.130 --> 39:19.861
I--I have baggage.

39:21.270 --> 39:25.229
And it comes with me
wherever I go.

39:25.270 --> 39:28.922
And to be honest,
I'm so tired of

39:28.970 --> 39:31.928
dragging it around with me.

39:33.450 --> 39:36.055
- Is that an overnight bag?

39:36.110 --> 39:38.066
- Yes.

39:38.110 --> 39:40.897
I have literally brought
my baggage with me.

39:43.200 --> 39:44.451
But only 'cause there's

39:44.510 --> 39:46.330
a Radiohead concert
in Philadelphia.

39:47.950 --> 39:50.418
Any interest in going with me?

39:50.470 --> 39:53.075
- I took it for love

39:53.120 --> 39:56.248
Or at least something
beautiful

39:59.830 --> 40:02.082
- Of all the windows
in all the hallways

40:02.130 --> 40:04.086
in this hospital,

40:04.140 --> 40:05.914
you had to stand
in front of mine.

40:05.960 --> 40:08.485
Get your own window.

40:08.530 --> 40:11.055
- I needed your advice today,
my friend,

40:11.100 --> 40:14.274
but you were busy.

40:14.320 --> 40:16.402
- Yeah, I mean,
that happens sometimes.

40:17.980 --> 40:21.939
- As a result,
I managed to lose

40:21.980 --> 40:24.494
my only friend

40:24.550 --> 40:26.450
and my only son.

40:27.990 --> 40:29.241
- I'm sure it's not that bad.

40:30.990 --> 40:33.151
- It is that bad.

40:33.210 --> 40:35.519
- Oh.

40:35.560 --> 40:37.460
Okay, sorry.

40:41.430 --> 40:42.988
- So what do I do now?

40:47.050 --> 40:50.008
Iggy, I need you to help me.

40:52.050 --> 40:54.439
- Okay.

40:58.840 --> 41:01.149
- Where have you been

41:01.190 --> 41:04.455
And what have you done

41:07.550 --> 41:08.972
- How's the VIP?

41:10.590 --> 41:13.024
Not feeling
very important.

41:14.380 --> 41:15.984
- Well, you are,

41:16.030 --> 41:19.113
to me,
to everyone.

41:22.130 --> 41:26.908
It's gonna be hard,
but...when you make it...

41:28.310 --> 41:29.959
Your job's gonna be right here
waiting for you.

41:32.220 --> 41:34.962
- My job means everything
to me, Max.

41:37.400 --> 41:39.618
- I know the feeling.

41:42.970 --> 41:47.623
- Moving pictures

41:47.670 --> 41:52.198
In silent films
